---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — Nhung Luong"
  description="About Nhung Luong, a data and AI engineer writing about pipelines, models, and data products."
>
  <article class="article">
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="article-body">
      <img
        src="/images/nhung.jpeg"
        alt="Nhung Luong"
        class="about-photo"
        width="1024"
        height="768"
      />
      <p>
        I'm a Senior Engineering Manager at Techcombank in Hanoi, where I lead
        a Data & AI engineering team. My work covers the pipelines that move data,
        the knowledge bases that give it structure and context, the models and AI
        agents built on top of it, and the products that deliver all of this to
        business users.
      </p>
      <h2>Career journey</h2>
      <p>
        My path into data wasn't a straight line. Six years in accounting and finance
        at Japanese companies like Honda and Panasonic taught me how businesses actually
        use numbers — a perspective I still rely on today, leading teams that build
        large-scale data platforms on AWS and Databricks at Techcombank.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Auditor — VACO Auditing Company Limited</strong><br />
        Performed statutory and financial statement audits for corporate clients,
        testing controls, verifying balances, and preparing audit documentation to
        Vietnamese and international standards.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Accountant — Honda, Panasonic</strong><br />
        Handled general accounting, month-end close, reconciliations, and management
        reporting for the finance function of large Japanese manufacturers, working
        closely with business units on cost and performance analysis.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Lead Data Analyst cum Data Engineer — Honda</strong><br />
        Bridged finance and engineering: built reporting and analytics for business
        stakeholders while developing the data pipelines and models behind them. This
        was the transition point from finance into data.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Senior Data Engineer → Senior Cloud Engineer → Engineering Manager →
        Senior Engineering Manager — Techcombank</strong><br />
        Progressed from designing and building large-scale data pipelines, to
        architecting cloud data infrastructure on AWS and Databricks, to leading
        engineering teams delivering data platforms, knowledge bases, AI agents, and
        data products for business users across the bank.
      </p>
      <h2>Key achievements</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Scaled the data and AI engineering team from 4 to 32 people, growing
          hiring, onboarding, and delivery structures alongside the headcount.
        </li>
        <li>
          Built the data lake on a medallion architecture, organizing data
          across bronze, silver, and gold layers to keep raw ingestion,
          cleansing, and business-ready datasets cleanly separated.
        </li>
        <li>
          Developed a Databricks-based framework for ingesting, transforming,
          and serving data between the data lake and the bank's surrounding
          systems.
        </li>
        <li>
          Designed and delivered the migration from AWS Glue to Databricks,
          moving both data and pipelines onto a single platform.
        </li>
        <li>
          Led the migration from the legacy data warehouse to the data lake,
          enabling the warehouse to be decommissioned.
        </li>
        <li>
          Introduced AI across the software development lifecycle — from
          requirements analysis and data discovery through implementation,
          testing, and deployment — to shorten delivery cycles.
        </li>
        <li>
          Built an internal wiki platform that lets teams create, publish,
          manage, and share their own knowledge bases — with an MCP server on
          top so AI agents can consume the same content programmatically.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>MSc in Banking and Finance — Sheffield Hallam University, United Kingdom</li>
        <li>Bachelor's Degree in Accounting and Auditing — National Economics University, Hanoi, Vietnam</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Find me</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/nhungluong1989/">GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nhung-luong-3614bb113/">LinkedIn</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
